columns.name: adsh
columns.dc:description: Accession Number. The 20-character string formed from the 18-digit number assigned by the Commission to each EDGAR submission.

columns.name: cik
columns.dc:description: Central Index Key (CIK). Ten digit number assigned by the Commission to each registrant that submits filings.

columns.name: name
columns.dc:description: Name of registrant. This corresponds to the name of the legal entity as recorded in EDGAR as of the filing date.

columns.name: countryba
columns.dc:description: The ISO 3166-1 country of the registrant's business address.

columns.name: stprba
columns.dc:description: The state or province of the registrant's business address, if field countryba is US or CA.

columns.name: cityba
columns.dc:description: The city of the registrant's business address.

columns.name: zipba
titles: Business Address Zip or Postal Code
columns.dc:description: The zip code of the registrant's business address.

columns.name: bas1
columns.dc:description: The first line of the street of the registrant's business address.

columns.name: bas2
columns.dc:description: The second line of the street of the registrant's business address.

columns.name: baph
columns.dc:description: The phone number of the registrant's business address.

columns.name: countryma
columns.dc:description: The ISO 3166-1 country of the registrant's mailing address.

columns.name: stprma
columns.dc:description: The state or province of the registrant's mailing address, if field countryma is US or CA.

columns.name: cityma
columns.dc:description: The city of the registrant's mailing address.

columns.name: zipma
titles: Mailing Address Zip or Postal Code
columns.dc:description: The zip code of the registrant's mailing address.

columns.name: mas1
columns.dc:description: The first line of the street of the registrant's mailing address.

columns.name: mas2
columns.dc:description: The second line of the street of the registrant's mailing address.

columns.name: countryinc
columns.dc:description: The country of incorporation for the registrant.

columns.name: stprinc
columns.dc:description: The state or province of incorporation for the registrant, if countryinc is US or CA, otherwise NULL.

columns.name: ein
columns.dc:description: Employee Identification Number, 9 digit identification number assigned by the Internal Revenue Service to business entities operating in the United States.

columns.name: former
columns.dc:description: Most recent former name of the registrant, if any.

columns.name: changed
columns.dc:description: Date of change from the former name, if any.

columns.name: fye
columns.dc:description: Fiscal Year End Date.

columns.name: form
columns.dc:description: The submission type of the registrant's filing.

columns.name: pdate
columns.dc:description: The date of the prospectus.

columns.name: effdate
columns.dc:description: The effective date of the prospectus or amendment.

columns.name: filed
columns.dc:description: The date of the registrant's filing with the Commission.

columns.name: accepted
columns.dc:description: The acceptance date and time of the registrant's filing with the Commission. Filings accepted after 5:30pm EST are considered filed on the following business day.

columns.name: instance
columns.dc:description: The name of the submitted XBRL Instance Document (EX-101.INS) type data file. The name often begins with the company ticker symbol.

columns.name: nciks
columns.dc:description: Number of Central Index Keys (CIK) of registrants (i.e., business units) included in the consolidating entity's submitted filing.

columns.name: aciks
columns.dc:description: Additional CIKs of co-registrants included in a consolidating entity's EDGAR submission, separated by spaces. If there are no other co-registrants (i.e., nciks = 1), the value of aciks is NULL. For a very small number of filers, the list of co-registrants is too long to fit in the field. Where this is the case, PARTIAL will appear at the end of the list indicating that not all co-registrants' CIKs are included in the field; users should refer to the complete submission file for all CIK information.

columns.name: tag
columns.dc:description: The unique identifier (name) for a tag in a specific taxonomy release.

columns.name: version
columns.dc:description: For a standard tag, an identifier for the taxonomy; otherwise the accession number where the tag was defined.

columns.name: custom
columns.dc:description: 1 if tag is custom (version=adsh), 0 if it is standard. Note: This flag is technically redundant with the version and adsh fields.

columns.name: abstract
columns.dc:description: 1 if the tag is not used to represent a numeric fact.

columns.name: datatype
columns.dc:description: If abstract=1, then NULL, otherwise the data type (e.g., monetary) for the tag.

columns.name: iord
columns.dc:description: If abstract=1, then NULL; otherwise, I if the value is a point in time, or D if the value is a duration.

columns.name: tlabel
columns.dc:description: If a standard tag, then the label text provided by the taxonomy, otherwise the text provided by the filer. A tag which had neither would have a NULL value here.

columns.name: doc
columns.dc:description: The detailed definition for the tag, truncated to 2048 characters. If a standard tag, then the text provided by the taxonomy, otherwise the text assigned by the filer. Some tags have neither, in which case this field is NULL.

columns.name: adsh
columns.dc:description: Accession Number. The 20-character string formed from the 18-digit number assigned by the Commission to each EDGAR submission.

columns.name: grp
columns.dc:description: Sequential number for grouping arcs in a submission.

columns.name: arc
columns.dc:description: Sequential number for arcs within a group in a submission.

columns.name: negative
columns.dc:description: Indicates a weight of -1 (TRUE if the arc is negative), but typically +1 (FALSE).

columns.name: ptag
columns.dc:description: The tag for the parent of the arc

columns.name: pversion
columns.dc:description: The version of the tag for the parent of the arc

columns.name: ctag
columns.dc:description: The tag for the child of the arc

columns.name: cversion
columns.dc:description: The version of the tag for the child of the arc

columns.name: adsh
columns.dc:description: Accession Number. The 20-character string formed from the 18-digit number assigned by the Commission to each EDGAR submission.

columns.name: tag
columns.dc:description: The unique identifier (name) for a tag in a specific taxonomy release.

columns.name: version
columns.dc:description: For a standard tag, an identifier for the taxonomy; otherwise the accession number where the tag was defined.

columns.name: ddate
columns.dc:description: The end date for the data value, rounded to the nearest month end.

columns.name: uom
columns.dc:description: The unit of measure for the value.

columns.name: series
columns.dc:description: The EDGAR assigned Series ID for the fund.

columns.name: class
columns.dc:description: The EDGAR assigned Class ID for the fund.

columns.name: measure
columns.dc:description: The Performance Measure has values that distinguish different returns according to whether they are Before Taxes (NULL), After Taxes on Distributions, After Taxes on Distributions and Sales, or are a pre-tax measure of returns based on a broadly available market index.

columns.name: document
columns.dc:description: A single series, or different classes of the same series, may be presented in different prospectuses, all in the same XBRL instance.  To define a distinct Risk/Return Summary for each prospectus, the preparer declares members of the Document Information Axis.

columns.name: otherdims
columns.dc:description: The preparer may declare additional axes and members of those axes to distinguish otherwise identical facts.

columns.name: iprx
columns.dc:description: A positive integer to distinguish different reported facts that otherwise would have the same primary key. For most purposes, data with iprx greater than 1 are not needed. The priority for the fact based on higher precision.

columns.name: value
columns.dc:description: The value. This is not scaled, it is as found in the Interactive Data file, but is rounded to four digits to the right of the decimal point.

columns.name: footnote
columns.dc:description: The plain text of any superscripted footnotes on the value, if any, as shown on the statement page, truncated to 512 characters.

columns.name: footlen
columns.dc:description: Number of characters in the plain text of the footnote prior to truncation; zero if no footnote.

columns.name: dimn
columns.dc:description: Small integer representing the number of dimensions. Note that this value is a function of the dimension segments.

columns.name: dcml
columns.dc:description: The value of the fact "decimals" attribute, with INF represented by 32767.

columns.name: adsh
columns.dc:description: Accession Number. The 20-character string formed from the 18-digit number assigned by the Commission to each EDGAR submission.

columns.name: tag
columns.dc:description: The unique identifier (name) for a tag in a specific taxonomy release.

columns.name: version
columns.dc:description: For a standard tag, an identifier for the taxonomy; otherwise the accession number where the tag was defined. For example, "invest/2013" indicates that the tag is defined in the 2013 INVEST taxonomy.

columns.name: ddate
columns.dc:description: The end date for the data value, rounded to the nearest month end.

columns.name: series
columns.dc:description: The EDGAR assigned Series ID for the fund.

columns.name: class
columns.dc:description: The EDGAR assigned Class ID for the fund.

columns.name: measure
columns.dc:description: The Performance Measure has values that distinguish different returns according to whether they are Before Taxes (NULL), After Taxes on Distributions, After Taxes on Distributions and Sales, or are a pre-tax measure of returns based on a broadly available market index.

columns.name: lang
columns.dc:description: The ISO language code of the fact content.

columns.name: iprx
columns.dc:description: A positive integer to distinguish different reported facts that otherwise would have the same primary key. For most purposes, data with iprx greater than 1 are not needed. The priority for the fact based on higher precision, closeness of the end date to a month end, and closeness of the duration to a multiple of three months. See fields dcml, durp and datp below.

columns.name: dcml
columns.dc:description: The value of the fact "xml:lang" attribute, en-US represented by 32767, other "en" dialects having lower values, and other languages lower still.

columns.name: dimn
columns.dc:description: Small integer representing the number of dimensions, useful for sorting. Note that this value is function of the dimension segments.

columns.name: escaped
columns.dc:description: Flag indicating whether the value has had tags removed.

columns.name: srclen
columns.dc:description: Number of characters in the original, unprocessed value. Zero indicates a NULL value.

columns.name: txtlen
columns.dc:description: The original length of the whitespace normalized value, which may have been greater than 8192.

columns.name: footnote
columns.dc:description: The plain text of any superscripted footnotes on the value, as shown on the page, truncated to 512 characters, or if there is no footnote, then this field will be blank.

columns.name: footlen
columns.dc:description: Number of characters in the plain text of the footnote prior to truncation.

columns.name: context
columns.dc:description: The value of the contextRef attribute in the source XBRL document, which can be used to recover the original HTML tagging if desired.

columns.name: value
columns.dc:description: The value, with all whitespace normalized, that is, all sequences of line feeds, carriage returns, tabs, non-breaking spaces, and spaces having been collapsed to a single space, and no leading or trailing spaces. Escaped XML that appears in EDGAR "Text Block" tags is processed to remove all mark-up (comments, processing instructions, elements, attributes). The value is truncated to a maximum number of bytes. The resulting text is not intended for end user display but only for text analysis applications.

columns.name: adsh
columns.dc:description: Accession Number. The 20-character string formed from the 18-digit number assigned by the Commission to each EDGAR submission.

columns.name: tag
columns.dc:description: The unique identifier (name) for a tag in a specific taxonomy release.

columns.name: version
columns.dc:description: For a standard tag, an identifier for the taxonomy; otherwise the accession number where the tag was defined. For example, "rr/2018" indicates that the tag is defined in the 2018 RR taxonomy.

columns.name: std
columns.dc:description: Standard label for a concept.

columns.name: terse
columns.dc:description: Short label for a Concept, often omitting text that should be inferable when the concept is reported in the context of other related concepts.

columns.name: verbose
columns.dc:description: Extended label for a Concept, making sure not to omit text that is required to enable the label to be understood on a stand alone basis.

columns.name: total
columns.dc:description: The label for a concept for use in presenting values associated with the concept when it is being reported as the total of a set of other values.

columns.name: negated
columns.dc:description: Label for a concept when it is to be presented with its fact value multiplied by -1.

columns.name: negatedTerse
columns.dc:description: Label for a concept when it is to be presented with its fact value multiplied by -1, often omitting text that should be inferable when the concept is reported in the context of other related concepts.
